Simple and tasty. The first time I made this recipe I used orange juice instead of lemons. Makes for a gentler flavour taht is also very pleasant.

Rating: 3
This was an elegant and easy dessert. Next time I'll grate the lemon peel instead of mincing it, and use a little less than the 2-1/2 teaspoons called for in the recipe.

Rating: 4
A delicious and elegant dessert! I made this for guests and everyone loved it. I prepared the egg yolk portion ahead of time, had the ramekins all ready, and preheated the oven during dinner. After dinner I only had to whip the egg whites and fold them in, then bake the souffles. This is a very tart-sweet dish with lively flavors. It was too tart for my two-year-old, but that's okay -- for once I was able to have my dessert all to myself!